{"questionId":"14619714","questionHtml":"<p>In the following triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ABC</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mi>cm</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/d3ca53d26c7b4e53b0081445ea5b9d4e4f4bfd59.png\" width=\"664\" height=\"200\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Find the area of triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ABC</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use Pythagoras’ theorem in a right-angled triangle.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><msqrt><mn>24</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the Pythagorean identity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>24</mn></msqrt><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></strong>&nbsp;(may be seen in area formula)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use 'Area<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>C</mi></math>'&nbsp;(must include their calculated value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>24</mn></msqrt><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp;(cm<sup>2</sup>)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">&nbsp;<strong><em>[6 marks]</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find perpendicular height of triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BAC</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>height</mtext><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to use the Pythagorean identity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>height</mtext><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(A1)</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>24</mn></msqrt><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em> A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>adjacent</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use Pythagoras’ theorem in a right-angled triangle.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>height</mtext><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(may be seen in area formula)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use 'Area<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mtext>base</mtext><mo>×</mo><mtext>height</mtext></math>'&nbsp;&nbsp;(must include their calculated value for height)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp;(cm<sup>2</sup>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14619714","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ1.4","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"In the following triangle ABC, AB=6cm, AC=10 cm and cos BAˆC=15. Find the area of triangle ABC.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"4","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles"],"memberS